FBIS4-28707 "dreas113__a94003" FBIS-EAS-94-113-A Daily Report 13 June 1994 ANNEX Japan Reportage on Issues Related to DPRK Continues Reportage on Issues Related to DPRK Continues MOFA: Carter `Might Stop Over' in Tokyo OW1106051894 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 11 Jun 94-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW1106051894 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database Japanese BFN [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 10 Jun 94 Evening Edition] [Text] A top official of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs [MOFA] revealed on 10 June that former U.S. President Jimmy Carter might stop over in Japan on his way home from a visit to the DPRK (North Korea) and South Korea next week. If he does stop over, he is expected to meet with Foreign Minister Koji Kakizawa.
